column2: Water skiers on lake before reading and 4" of rain day before.
Sunny and clear- and no activity on the lake.
Clear and calm- and no activity on the lake.
Weather Clear / A lot of activity on lake
Sunny 75 Calm Water very high - half way up 2x6 on dock
New eagle nest in top of large white pine on Emma Isaland.
Lake up 8" due to storm on 8/7

Peter Howe and Jim Gammon did the Temperature and D.O. (Pete's depth rope not quite long enough to reach bottom). Lake extremely high due to recent rains. Secchi 2 feet less than previous. Pete and Jim could see algae in the water column. Probably the worst mid-summer water clarity I've seen since I started monitoring.

column1: Note: D.O. data are suspect: Pete's device wasn't working properly. One week later there were fish on the bottom (34-37 ft) per Hummingbird locator. This shouldn't be possible if D.O. was zero.

column2: Small ( less than 1mm) microorganisms in water column- silver in color- look like little birds
Sunny- nearly calm. Did invasive survey. 3 otters.
Windy. Visibility down into water was reduced- but still could see secchi disk. Digital thermometer failed - used thermometer in Varn Dorn sampler.
Partly sunny- Windy - more than  calm
